##

EXAMPLE: countdown_loop.stult

This code counts down from a fixed number and then prints a message
when the countdown is complete.

It demonstrates the use of while-style loops, mutable counters, compound assignment,
after-loop blocks, outer-scope writes with @ and explicit outer-scope reads with @.

##

WRITE_LINE : STD["IO"]["OUTPUT"]["WRITE_LINE"]

ITERATIONS : 10

i : ITERATIONS

((i > 0)) {
    # Using the at symbol tells the interpreter that we want to access a variable from outside the current scope.
    # The at symbol is optional for reads, but required for writes.

    @WRITE_LINE(@i) 

    @i :- 1
},{
	# Code within this block runs just once when the conditional no longer holds true.

    @WRITE_LINE("")
	@WRITE_LINE("THE COUNT IS OVER. PACK UP AND GO HOME.")
}